OL,3,CResident doctors in England to strike
OL,4,Cfor six days after Easter
OL,6,FHealth Secretary Wes Streeting
OL,7,Fhighlighted how the Government chose
OL,8,Fto maintain as much pre-planned care
OL,9,Fas possible during previous rounds of
OL,10,Findustrial action, during a speech,
OL,11,Fearlier on Wednesday.
OL,13,FHe said: "Under our predecessors,
OL,14,Fthere was an acceptance that when
OL,15,Fdoctors go on strike, planned
OL,16,Foperations just get cancelled, as if
OL,17,Fthese were pain-free, consequence-free
OL,18,Fcancellations for patients.
OL,26,@uD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1774508671
OL,3,CResident doctors in England to strike
OL,4,Cfor six days after Easter
OL,6,F"We didn't accept that and we made the
OL,7,Fsafety case for maintaining planned
OL,8,Fcare, keeping 95% of activity going,
OL,9,Feven during strikes."
OL,11,FThe Department of Health and Social
OL,12,FCare has been contacted for comment.
